A healthcare worker places a COVID-19 PCR test vial into a bag for transportation. AFP/Patrick T. Fallon JOHANNESBURG - There are just under 989 new COVID-19 cases. Sadly, one person has died in the past 48 hours. WATCH: Clerics unhappy with COVID-19 regulations The cumulative number of deaths in South Africa now stands at almost 100,000 people. Gauteng has the most new cases at present at 362, followed by the Western Cape with 286 and then KwaZulu-Natal with 199. The positivity rate stands at 5.9 percent and 16,849 tests were conducted in the last 24 hours. As of today the cumulative number of #COVID19 cases identified in SA is 3 713 252 with 989 new cases reported. Today 01 deaths have been reported bringing the total to 99 966 deaths. The cumulative number of recoveries now stand at 3 599 563 with a recovery rate of 96.9% pic.twitter.com/zctTiYXG4X